intro:
Until now `click.actions` fired on **any** click. To react differently to different mouse buttons, nest under `left`, `right`, `middle`, `drop`, `shiftLeft`, `shiftRight`:

```
click {
  left {
    actions {
      message = "Left clicked!"
    }
  }
  right {
    actions {
      message = "Right clicked!"
    }
  }
}
```

Classic shop pattern: left-click to buy, right-click to inspect.

```
click {
  left  { actions { command = "give @p diamond_sword 1" } }
  right { actions { message = "Costs 10 emeralds" } }
}
```

If you also have a top-level `click.actions` and a `click.left.actions`, both fire on a left click - the top-level one is the catch-all.

**Goal:** split the existing `click.actions` into two distinct handlers - `left` runs the `command`, `right` shows a `message = "Costs 10 emeralds"`.

